name: French Creek
comment: Zack and I had our first campout here with PIC in a Group Camping site. It was also the fIrst state park that Zack and I used extensively when he was growing up. Favorite places included Miller's Point and Hopewell Lake.

name: Lehigh Gorge - Rockport Access
comment: Rockport is one of 3 entrances to the park. It is administered from nearby Hickory Run State Park.

name: Hopewell Furnace
comment: Located in southeastern Berks County, near Elverson, Pennsylvania, is an example of an American 19th century rural "iron plantation". The buildings include a blast furnace, and auxiliary structures.

name: Dead Man's Hollow Conservation Area
comment: Maintained by Allegheny Land Trust. Several ruins on the trails.

name: Loyalsock State Forest
comment: Address is for Loyalsock District Office.

name: Pine Grove Furnace
comment: This 696-acre park features Laurel Lake, Fuller Lake, hiking, biking & the Appalachian Trail Museum. Park is surrounded by Michaux State Forest. Recommended Visits: Pole Steeple Vista at sunset, Sunset Rocks, Tumbling Run, and the AT Museum.

name: Worlds End
comment: Zack and I have been here a few times. I have a picture of him fly fishing here. Local restaurants: High Knobb Inn, Forksville General Store, Forksville Inn, Hillsgrove Hotel, The Barn Tavern. Crestmont inn Eaglesmere, really good meals, a little bit more higher end but worth it. Also, see < https://uncoveringpa.com/things-to-do-in-worlds-end-state-park >.

name: Rolling Hill Park
comment: Head out on the blue trail that leads to Mill Creek where you'll find jaw dropping ruins that date back to the early 20th century.

name: Elk State Forest
comment: Start this 16-mile backpack from the trailhead on PA 555 and tackle some of the countryâ€™s newest elk habitat. Go in October for bugling.

name: Hickory Run State Park
comment: Boulder field is a great feature. Want to check out 'Shades of Death' Trail.

name: Moosic Mountain
address: Lackawanna County, eight miles northeast from the city of Scranton, entrance off PA-247.
comment: Nature Conservancy Preserve is one of the best locations in the northeastern U.S. for heath barrens.
